                "type": "textBox",
                "value": [
                    {
                        "type": "subTextBox",
                        "value": "I love wandering through supermarkets - plenty of creative inspiration and, occasionally, a showcase of what not to do."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "subTextBox",
                        "value": "But then I stumble upon these packaging disasters, and I can’t help but wonder: how do they actually get a green light from their management?"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "subTextBox",
                        "value": "Seriously, someone in a meeting said, “Yes, let’s roll this out.” And then those same people have to double down on damage control post-launch. It’s almost like a self-inflicted PR stunt."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "subTextBox",
                        "value": "As I always say, the devil is in the details when it comes to crafting a brand identity that sticks. Ignoring the tiny, intricate elements can quickly turn a “wow” into a “whoops.”"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "subTextBox",
                        "value": "Here are a few prime examples that scream why R&D should come before design. It’s easy to get swept up in the aesthetics - cool fonts, flashy packaging styles - but none of that secures brand loyalty or recognition if the basics are botched."
                    }
                ]
            },
